###### 3.1.3 Space and Time *Complexity* of *Tree-Recursive* Fibonacci Process

From Fig. 1.2.2.1 we see that the *space* complexity is $O(n)$ and the *time* complexity is $O(2^n)$. *Space* complexity is a function of the *height* of the process tree, whereas *time* complexity a function of the *width* of the tree:

- space complexity : $O(n)$
- time complexity : $O(2^n)$

The computation process is highly inefficient. The right subtree $fib(3)$ appears identically as a subtree in the left subtree of $fib(4)$. Furthermore e.g. $fib(2)$ is computed three times.

"

