###### 3.1.4 *Space* and *Time Complixity* of Closed Form Fibonacci Approximation

A *nonrecursive* approximation to $fib(n)$ is its nearest integer $f_{fib}(n)$:

$f : \mathbb N \rightarrow \mathbb N$

$f : n \mapsto f_{fib}(n)$

$f_{fib}(n) := \left\lceil\frac{\psi^n}{\sqrt{5}}\right\rfloor \text{ for } n \ge 0$

where:

$\psi := \frac{1+\sqrt{5}}{2} = 1.618033988749895$ 

is the [*golden ratio*](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_ratio) and

$\psi = \lim\limits_{x \to \infty}\frac{f_{fib}(n+1)}{f_{fib}(n)}$

more info about Fibonacci numbers can be found [here](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_number). 

From the formula for $f_{fib}(n)$ we see that the *space complexity* is $O(1)$ and *time complexity* $O(\psi^n)$.

"

# ╔═╡ d18098af-8fbb-4579-baef-b8579a33c02b
const ϕ = (1 + √5) / 2.0          # golden ratio as a Float

# ╔═╡ 2a62d948-fc66-4dc4-be49-3d5d6fc6bfda
const ψ = (1 - √5) / 2.0 

# ╔═╡ 30817bee-f3f5-4e1e-9672-8feef1a1a098
const sqrtOf5 = √5        

# ╔═╡ 59f4bd16-f5fd-43a0-9130-733b318bb850
function fib2(n)                  # in infix notation
	f_n = ϕ^n / sqrtOf5           # a Float number
	convert(Int64, round(f_n))    # rounding to integer
end # function fib2

