###### 3.1.5 Closed Form Fibonacci Approximation: [*Binet*'s Formula](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_sequence)

Binet's formula is also a *nonrecursive* approximation to $fib(n)$ is its nearest integer $f_{fib}(n)$:

$f : \mathbb N \rightarrow \mathbb N$

$f : n \mapsto f_{fib}(n)$

$f_{fib}(n) := \left\lceil\frac{\phi^n - \psi^n}{\sqrt{5}}\right\rfloor \text{ for } n \ge 0$

where:

$\phi := \frac{1+\sqrt{5}}{2} =  1.618033988749895$

$\psi := \frac{1-\sqrt{5}}{2} = -0.6180339887498949$

more info can be found [here](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibonacci_number). From the formula for $f_{fib}(n)$ we see that the *space complexity* is $O(1)$ and *time compexity* $O(n)$.

"

# ╔═╡ be5953f4-8ee2-4b8e-a6d4-f93eb8b9971e
function fib3(n)                 
	f_n = (ϕ^n - ψ^n) / sqrtOf5      # a Float number is generated
	convert(Int64, round(f_n))
end # function fib3

